  "texts": [
    "This improvement indicates the removal of blocking Bi 25 FeO 39 domains and the formation of well-connected, phase-pure BiFeO 3 grains.",
    "The corresponding dielectric response exhibits a near-Debye CPE exponent (n = 0.909), a small prefactor (Q ≈ 3 × 10 -10 S•s n), and a reduced effective capacitance (C eff ≈ 10 -10 F), all of which are indication of homogeneous, low-defect grain interiors.",
    "The resulting enhancement in bulk AC conductivity-from 3.12 × 10 -8 to 7.81 × 10 -5 S m -1 -correlates strongly with the lattice contraction and Raman A 1 -mode sharpening that signify reduced strain and strengthened Bi-O bonding.At 725 • C, the same composition exhibits a massive semicircle (radius ∼ 1.44 × 10 9 Ω), reflecting the persistence of insulating impurity phases that limit charge percolation, even though the CPE ex-ponent remains high (n = 0.976).",
    "Upon sintering at 775 • C, a second, low-frequency arc appears with n = 0.767 and C eff ∼ 10 -7 F, probably because of a thin Bi 2 O 3 -rich intergranular film formed during liquid-phase-assisted densification; however, this contribution is minor relative to the dominant bulk relaxation.In contrast, the Bi-rich 70: 30 ceramics exhibit persistent structural disorder across both sintering temperatures.",
    "At 725 • C, the low-frequency arc is highly depressed (n = 0.427, ϕ > 50 •) and accompanied by a large CPE prefactor (Q ≈ 8.7 × 10 -8 S•s n), indicating a broad distribution of relaxation times associated with defective, compositionally inhomogeneous grain boundaries enriched in Bi 3+ antisites and Fe-oxidised species-consistent with their expanded lattice parameters and broadened Raman modes."
